  "doc_id": "44353",
  "text": "For enzymatic activity, lung rudiments and fibroblasts were homogenized in 2 ml (tissue) or in 1 ml (fibroblasts) of 0.1 M citrate/0.2 M phosphate buffer, pH 4.5, then centrifuged at 25,000 g for 10 min and the supernatants were used. In preliminary experiments, no enzymatic activity was detected in the sediments. ß-N-acetyl-glucosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.30), ß-D-glucuronidase (EC 3.2.1.31), ß-Nacetyl-galactosaminidase (EC 3.2.1.53) and ß-galactosidase (EC 3.2.1.23) were assayed as previously described by [CITATION_1] using, respectively, as substrates 4-methyl-umbelliferyl-ß-N-acetyl glucosaminide, 4-methyl-umbelliferyl-ß-D-glucuronide, 4-methyl-umbelliferil-ß-N-acetylgalactosaminide 4-methyl-umbelliferyl-ß-galactoside in 0.1 M citrate/0.2 M phosphate buffer, pH 4.5, and 50 µl of enzyme preparation. One enzyme unit is defined as the amount of the enzyme that converts 1 nmol/hr of substrate into 4-methyl-umbelliferone at 37°C. Specific activity is expressed as units/mg protein. Proteins were determined according to the Bradford method (1976) using cristalline calf gamma globuline (Merck) as standard.",
  "correct_citation": {
